The Library of Congress Classification (LCC) is a system used to organize books and other materials on the shelves of libraries. It is widely used in academic, research, and government libraries.

Here are the main categories in the LCC:

* A - Philosophy
* B - History
* C - Auxiliary sciences of history
* D - World history and history of Europe, Asia, Africa, Australia, Pacific Area, etc.
* E-F - Local history and genealogy
* G-H - Science
* I-J - Technology (General)
* K-Z - General works

For more information about the LCC, you can visit the Library of Congress website: https://www.loc.gov/catdir/cpso/lcco/.
